data.name: Teriyaki Chicken with Steamed Rice and Broccoli
data.quickTastyDescription: A delightful combination of tender teriyaki chicken, fluffy steamed rice, and vibrant broccoli, perfect for a quick and satisfying meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Start by marinating the chicken breast in teriyaki sauce for at least 10 minutes.
While the chicken is marinating, prepare the rice according to package instructions.
In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat and cook the marinated chicken for about 6-7 minutes on each side until fully cooked.
In the last 5 minutes of cooking, add broccoli florets to the skillet to steam alongside the chicken, covered.
Once everything is cooked, serve the teriyaki chicken over the steamed rice, with broccoli on the side.
Garnish with sesame seeds before serving.
